  "body": "Since https://github.com/blockscout/blockscout/pull/4908, Blockscout now comply to the Etherscan contract verification API.\r\nIt's now fairly easy to deploy a private testnets with an explorer that provides the same API as etherscan for the verification.\r\n\r\nThus, I think it might be interesting to be able configure the explorer url used for the verification on a custom network. \r\n\r\nAn example implementation I have in mind would be to add an optional `explorer` field on each networks:\r\n```typescript\r\nconst config: HardhatUserConfig = {\r\n  networks: {\r\n    privateNetwork: {\r\n      chainId: 1337,\r\n      explorer: {\r\n        apiURL: \"https://myprivate.network/api\",\r\n        browserURL: \"https://myprivate.network\"\r\n      }\r\n    },\r\n};\r\n```\r\nAt the moment, the only workaround I found was to modify `./packages/hardhat-etherscan/src/network/prober.ts` to manually add my custom explorer.\r\n\r\nIf you think it might be interesting, I should probably be able to implement this quickly .\r\n",
